snippet: The bank said the results were from cost-cutting and a strong performance by its Italian commercial bank as well as operations in Central Europe.
abstract: Italy's biggest banks benefit from recent stress test; UniCredit reports third-quarter profit of 722 million euros, or $900 million, up from 204 million euros in year-ago quarter.
lead_paragraph: The bank said the results were from cost-cutting and a strong performance by its Italian commercial bank as well as operations in Central Europe.

headline.main: Italy’s Biggest Banks Benefit From Stress Test
